```julia
function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(word[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` function from Julia's standard library to create a new collection containing only the words that satisfy the condition `isuppercase(word[1])`, which checks if the first character of the word is an uppercase letter. The resulting collection contains only the words that start with a capital letter.
